<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-06-11T17:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-06-11T17:36:00-05:00" n="211" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">701.1211/250: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-06-11T16:00:00-06:36"><hi rend="italic">June 11,
                                            1920—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 9:33
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>285. Mr. Fernando Iglesias Calderón has informed me unofficially that
                                Provisional President de la Huerta has selected him to go to
                                Washington as confidential agent of the present régime and that he
                                will leave for Washington by Laredo June 16th.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>